cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically sequence labeling tasks such as named entity recognition (NER) and chunking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural network architectures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses pre-trained word embeddings, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on two standard datasets, which could also suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
